  Peterson   2."]},{"name":"Peter","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Hans, Kurt, Otto, Ernst, Fritz, Heinz, Helmut, Horst, Kaspar, Klaus, Siegfried, Wolfgang.","English, Scottish, German, Dutch, French (Alsace and Lorraine), Czech (Moravian), Slovak, Croatian, and Slovenian; Hungarian (<b>Péter</b>): from the personal name <i>Peter</i> (Greek <i>Petros</i>, from <i>petra</i> ‘rock’). The personal name was popular throughout Christian Europe in the Middle Ages, having been bestowed by Christ as a byname on the apostle Simon bar Jonah, the brother of Andrew. The name was chosen by Christ for its symbolic significance (John 1:42, Matt. 16:18); Saint Peter is regarded as the founding head of the Christian Church in view of Christ's saying, ‘Thou art Peter and upon this rock I will build my Church’. In Christian Germany in the early Middle Ages this was the most frequent personal name of non-ancient Germanic origin until the 14th century. In North America, this surname has also absorbed cognates from other languages, for example Czech   Petr  , Polish <b>Piotr</b> and <b>Pietr</b>, Albanian <b>Pjetri</b> (from the personal name <i>Pjetër</i>, definite form <i>Pjetri</i>), and also their derivatives (see examples at   Peterson  ). It has also been adopted as a surname by Ashkenazic Jews."]}]},{"name":"Jön","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Simplified spelling of   John   or a short form of   Jonathan .  The name is borne by the Canadian singer  Jon Vickers  (  b. 1926 ) and the American actor  Jon Voight  (  b. 1938 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Jonathan","meanings":["Biblical name, meaning ‘God has given’, composed of the same elements as those of   Matthew  , but in reverse order. This is the name of several characters in the Bible, most notably a son of King Saul, who was a devoted friend and supporter of the young David, even when David and Saul were themselves at loggerheads (1 Samuel 31; 2 Samuel 1:19–26). The name is often taken as symbolic of steadfast friendship and loyalty. Well-known bearers of the name include the Irish clergyman and writer  Jonathan Swift  (  1667-1745 ), British theatre director  Jonathan Miller  (  b. 1934 ), British actor  Jonathan Pryce  (  b. 1947 ), and British television presenter  Jonathan Ross  (  b. 1960 )."]},{"name":"Jonn","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Jon   or  <b>John</b> ."]},{"name":"John","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1357049,"age":3,"year":"1323","julianDay":2204276,"description":"Sweden and Russia establish border.","jurisdictionLevel":3},{"id":1357050,"age":30,"year":"1350","julianDay":2214138,"description":"Black Death killed one-third of population.","jurisdictionLevel":3}],"lifeSummary":"Jön Petersson Baat av Flishult i Sandsjö was born in 1320, in Flishult, Näsby, Jönköping, Sweden. He had at least 1 daughter with Ingeborg Ormsdotter. He died on 6 July 1418, in Norra Sandsjö, Jönköping, Sweden, at the age of 98."},"et":{"1320–6 July 1418":"1320–6. juuli 1418","1325–Female":"1325–Surnud","1405–1463":"1405–1463","1320–1418":"1320–1418","1325":"1325","1323":"1323","1320":"1320","1463":"1463","6 July 1418":"6. juuli 1418","1350":"1350","1418":"1418","1405":"1405","Flishult, Näsby, Jönköping, Sweden":"Flishult, Näsby, Jönköping, Rootsi","Norra Sandsjö, Jönköping, Sweden":"Norra Sandsjö, Jönköping, Rootsi"},"fi":{"1320–6 July 1418":"1320–6. heinäkuuta 1418","1325–Female":"1325–Kuollut","1405–1463":"1405–1463","1320–1418":"1320–1418","1325":"1325","1323":"1323","1320":"1320","1463":"1463","6 July 1418":"6. heinäkuuta 1418","1350":"1350","1418":"1418","1405":"1405","Flishult, Näsby, Jönköping, Sweden":"Flishult, Näsby, Jönköping, Ruotsi","Norra Sandsjö, Jönköping, Sweden":"Norra Sandsjö, Jönköping, Ruotsi"},"fr":{"1320–6 July 141